The paper deals with statistical mixtures and information geometry, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Gaussian Mixture Models (GMMs) also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses divergence measures and inequalities, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and statistics (cs.SI).
